This is the specifications for Game 1 of the Track Cards Played challenge.  
In this game, the game opens in a new page with one hand of cards displayed vertically face down in the left half of the screen.  There are two optional ways to play chosen by the player at the start of the game.  The first way is all cards are overturned at once by player clicking on hand.  Optionally, the player can choose to have a fixed time for the cards to be displayed before they are overturned.  Or, the player will click on the hand to turn them over face down again.
In the right half of the screen, all possible cards for all suits will be displayed using the simple text, horizontal format.  The player will click on each simple text card that the player remembers from the hand in the left half of the screen.  If the player is correct, that card in the hand on the left will be turned face up.  If the player is incorrect, a message will be displayed that the player was incorrect.  A count of the incorrect choices will be displayed close to the right side of the screen